      "id": "adm-cycle",
      "title": "The ADM Cycle",
      "topic": "ADM",
      "description": "The Architecture Development Method (ADM) is the core process of TOGAF. The Preliminary Phase, shown outside the wheel above Phase A, establishes the architecture capability, tailors the method to the enterprise, and sets up the governance framework — it runs once at the start of an EA practice, not every cycle. The eight ADM phases A through H then run iteratively as a wheel: Phase A (Vision) scopes the engagement, Phases B-D develop the Business, Information Systems (Data + Application), and Technology architectures, Phase E identifies work packages and Transition Architectures, Phase F finalises the Implementation and Migration Plan, Phase G governs the implementation, and Phase H manages change after go-live. Requirements Management sits at the hub because it is a continuous process that interacts with every phase, not a stage of its own.",
      "svg": "<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 320 400\" class=\"svg-diagram\" role=\"img\" aria-label=\"TOGAF ADM cycle diagram: Preliminary phase sits above the wheel of eight phases A through H, which connect clockwise around the central Requirements Management circle\">\n  <defs>\n    <marker id=\"adm-arrowhead\" markerWidth=\"8\" markerHeight=\"8\" refX=\"7\" refY=\"3\" orient=\"auto\">\n      <path d=\"M0,0 L7,3 L0,6 Z\" fill=\"var(--accent)\" />\n    </marker>\n  </defs>\n  <g id=\"admRing\" data-diagram-build=\"adm-ring\"></g>\n  <circle cx=\"160\" cy=\"235\" r=\"42\" class=\"adm-core\" />\n  <text x=\"160\" y=\"231\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"adm-core-lbl\">Requirements</text>\n  <text x=\"160\" y=\"245\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"adm-core-lbl\">Management</text>\n</svg>",
